# Project Summary: SAFORA
Safora is a crowdsourced travel safety platform designed to help travelers share and receive real-time safety information.

## Core Features
- User Registration & Login
- Crowdsourced Safety Reports (Unsafe areas, accidents, road blockages, weather)
- Interactive Map showing safe/unsafe locations
- Community interaction (Comments, Ratings)
- Admin Moderation

## Proposed API Endpoints
### Authentication
- `POST /api/auth/register`: Register a new user.
- `POST /api/auth/login`: Authenticate user and return token.

### Reports
- `POST /api/reports`: Create a new safety report (requires title, type, description, location).
- `GET /api/reports`: Fetch all reports (with optional filters for location or type).
- `GET /api/reports/:id`: Get detailed information about a specific report.
- `PUT /api/reports/:id`: Update an existing report (reporter only).
- `DELETE /api/reports/:id`: Remove a report (reporter or admin).

### Community Interaction
- `POST /api/reports/:id/comments`: Add a comment to a report.
- `GET /api/reports/:id/comments`: Retrieve comments for a specific report.
- `POST /api/reports/:id/rate`: Rate a report as helpful or unhelpful.

### Alerts & Routes
- `GET /api/alerts`: Get real-time alerts for the user's current or specified location.
- `GET /api/routes/safe`: Get suggestions for safe travel routes based on community data.

### Admin
- `GET /api/admin/users`: List all registered users.
- `DELETE /api/admin/users/:id`: Delete a user account.
- `DELETE /api/admin/reports/:id`: Moderate and remove inappropriate or fake reports.

## Data Models
### User
- `name`, `email`, `password`, `role` (user/admin), `createdAt`
### Report
- `reporter` (Ref to User), `type` (Enum: Unsafe Area, Road Blockage, Weather, Accident, Tip), `description`, `location` (coordinates), `status`, `createdAt`
### Comment
- `report` (Ref to Report), `user` (Ref to User), `content`, `createdAt`
### Rating
- `report` (Ref to Report), `user` (Ref to User), `isHelpful` (Boolean), `createdAt`
